<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-23T22:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-23T22:36:00-05:00" n="882" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d882">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12967.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-23T21:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1914, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>This morning an opportunity was presented to ask the President regarding
                            the relations with Zapata. He replied that nothing has been arranged. I
                            understood that in the attempts so far there has been a lack of
                            confidence on each side. The President intimated that possibly the good
                            offices of the United States might be effective in arranging a
                            conference with Zapata and himself. It is a delicate matter but should
                            not be very difficult if handled with proper intelligence, discretion
                            and tact.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>